WEBVTT

00:00.918 --> 00:01.782
ANNOUNCER:
Previously on Slasher.

00:02.003 --> 00:04.244
CHILDREN: Trick or treat!

00:05.631 --> 00:06.541
[ Screams ]

00:06.883 --> 00:07.668
[ Groans]

00:08.050 --> 00:09.335
[ Screaming ]

00:09.343 --> 00:11.004
Oh, God! Stop!

00:12.972 --> 00:14.473
No, please! Stop!

00:15.266 --> 00:16.597
TRENT:DonT!No!

00:16.893 --> 00:18.383
[ Woman screaming ]

00:19.061 --> 00:20.597
Please! No!

00:21.314 --> 00:22.554
[ Screaming ]

00:22.565 --> 00:23.429
VAUGHN: Help me!

00:23.733 --> 00:24.848
[ Saw buzzing ]

00:26.194 --> 00:27.104
Sarah.

00:27.612 --> 00:28.522
Welcome home.

00:29.363 --> 00:31.103
You glow.

00:33.534 --> 00:35.274
Well, maybe you're the killer, Cam.

00:36.913 --> 00:38.574
He thinks this is over.

00:40.082 --> 00:41.788
It's not even close
to being over.

00:43.461 --> 00:45.326
[ Inaudible ]

00:45.338 --> 00:47.203
This town has been cleansed.

00:47.840 --> 00:49.296
"And the Lord said in His heart,

00:49.300 --> 00:51.586
'Never again will I curse
the ground for man's sake,

00:52.470 --> 00:54.381
nor will I again destroy
every living thing

00:54.388 --> 00:55.377
as I have done'. "

01:00.311 --> 01:01.767
[ Heavy breathing ]

01:37.473 --> 01:39.930
[ Heavy breathing continues ]

01:46.857 --> 01:48.142
[ Gasps ]
Jesus!

01:50.278 --> 01:51.313
My God, Cam.

01:51.320 --> 01:52.480
What is wrong with you?

01:54.490 --> 01:55.445
Wake up, Cam.

01:55.950 --> 01:56.780
Wake up!

01:57.702 --> 01:59.033
-Suzy, would you...
-Shit, Alan!

01:59.245 --> 02:00.530
Calm down.

02:01.831 --> 02:03.037
Where am I?

02:03.040 --> 02:03.950
You're sleepwalking.

02:04.500 --> 02:05.410
And you wanna know why?

02:05.668 --> 02:07.659
Because you were playing
goddamn videogames

02:07.670 --> 02:08.659
right before bed again.

02:08.671 --> 02:10.161
And I told you not to.

02:11.924 --> 02:13.630
If you would just frickin'
listen to me,

02:13.634 --> 02:14.965
we wouldn't have to
go through this

02:14.969 --> 02:16.584
every frickin' night.

02:17.597 --> 02:18.928
Oh, come on.

02:19.223 --> 02:20.463
You pissed yourself?

02:21.225 --> 02:23.967
You are too old for this.
What is wrong with you?

02:24.145 --> 02:25.635
I'm sorry, Mom.
I didn't mean to.

02:25.855 --> 02:27.595
Well, you did, Cam.
You did.

02:27.815 --> 02:30.227
And now I'm gonna have to
change all your sheets

02:30.234 --> 02:31.770
and wash them,
and your pj's, too.

02:31.777 --> 02:32.732
And I'm gonna be lucky

02:32.737 --> 02:34.398
if I get two hours
of goddamn sleep

02:34.405 --> 02:36.236
because you are
such a little baby!

02:36.657 --> 02:37.567
[ Sighs ]

02:37.575 --> 02:39.736
SUZY: I oughta, uh,
make you wear diapers.

02:40.119 --> 02:41.029
Would you like that?

02:41.037 --> 02:43.369
How would you like that?
Wearing diapers to bed.

02:44.665 --> 02:45.700
That's what I oughta do.

02:45.875 --> 02:47.206
I'm gonna make you
wear diapers to bed.

02:47.376 --> 02:49.367
And to school,
in front of all your friends.

02:49.587 --> 02:50.497
To teach you a lesson

02:50.504 --> 02:51.960
because you are such
a little baby!

02:52.548 --> 02:53.333
[ Screaming ]

02:53.758 --> 02:55.089
[ Grunting ]

02:56.302 --> 02:57.212
[ Snap ]

02:57.219 --> 02:58.345
ALAN: What the hell?

02:58.804 --> 03:00.010
Cam?

03:01.807 --> 03:03.092
Suzanne!

03:05.144 --> 03:06.429
Suzanne!

03:11.651 --> 03:12.936
What happened?

03:13.486 --> 03:15.101
Jesus, no.

03:15.363 --> 03:16.193
Suzanne.

03:17.281 --> 03:19.067
No! What have you done?

03:19.075 --> 03:19.905
No!

03:20.409 --> 03:21.444
Cameron!

03:22.161 --> 03:22.946
No!

03:24.955 --> 03:25.990
No!

03:34.590 --> 03:36.000
Oh, come on.
It's smiling.

03:36.884 --> 03:38.169
It's wrong.

03:38.344 --> 03:39.709
No, it's not.

03:40.012 --> 03:41.548
-It...
-Look at it.

03:45.267 --> 03:46.928
-A ridiculous smile.
-[ Laughs ]

03:47.770 --> 03:50.136
-Well, it's not very scary.
-[ Both laughing ]

03:51.691 --> 03:53.522
I bet you never thought
this was possible.

03:55.403 --> 03:56.392
Havin' fun...

03:56.946 --> 03:58.561
in Waterbury?

03:58.572 --> 04:00.358
Yeah, I guess I didn't.
[ Snickers ]

04:01.617 --> 04:02.823
[ Taps table ]

04:05.955 --> 04:07.286
Sarah.

04:08.874 --> 04:11.035
I know we both
lost people we love,

04:11.293 --> 04:12.248
this summer.

04:12.628 --> 04:13.663
[ Birds chirping ]

04:16.882 --> 04:17.667
But-II

04:19.468 --> 04:21.379
Waterbury...

04:22.012 --> 04:23.548
It had a problem.

04:24.432 --> 04:26.013
[ Scoffs ]
Lots of problems,

04:26.434 --> 04:27.765
lots of secrets...

04:28.144 --> 04:29.429
[ Birds chirping ]

04:30.604 --> 04:31.980
and, um...

04:35.609 --> 04:36.769
What?

04:38.446 --> 04:40.186
The Executioner...

04:42.283 --> 04:44.194
He kinda cleaned up this town.

04:44.994 --> 04:47.485
In his own sick way.

04:48.247 --> 04:49.487
I mean, yeah, but...

04:49.790 --> 04:51.496
murdering eight people?

04:51.792 --> 04:54.625
Yeah, I'm not condoning...
his actions.

04:56.297 --> 04:57.503
I'm just saying that...

04:58.507 --> 04:59.883
[ Sighs ]

05:00.176 --> 05:01.962
I don't, I don't know
what I'm saying.

05:01.969 --> 05:03.675
Forget it. Sorry.

05:04.555 --> 05:05.761
Yeah.

05:06.098 --> 05:07.304
What you're saying...

05:07.933 --> 05:08.968
I think you're right.

05:11.854 --> 05:15.017
There's a lot of darkness in this town,
and it's not just The Executioner.

05:31.749 --> 05:34.661
You two be helping me
hand out candy tomorrow or...?

05:34.835 --> 05:35.745
[ Sighs ]

05:35.753 --> 05:37.835
I don't know how many
trick or treaters we'll get.

05:38.172 --> 05:40.254
It's, uh...
it's Sarah's birthday,

05:40.758 --> 05:41.793
tomorrow.

05:41.801 --> 05:42.916
Oh, right. Right.

05:44.094 --> 05:45.504
Happy Birthday.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.715
Thank you.

05:51.060 --> 05:54.018
All right, so, you know,
I should... go back to work.

05:54.814 --> 05:56.145
Remember, scary, okay?

05:56.148 --> 05:57.308
Chase those demons away.

06:00.027 --> 06:01.187
[ Door opening ]

06:01.362 --> 06:03.523
She seems in fine spirits.

06:05.199 --> 06:06.029
Yeah.

06:07.368 --> 06:08.699
She is.

06:09.245 --> 06:10.075
[ Sighs ]

06:10.621 --> 06:11.861
"When the storm passes by,

06:13.123 --> 06:15.079
the wicked are gone."

06:16.710 --> 06:19.087
Proverbs 10:25.

06:21.131 --> 06:22.337
See?

06:22.883 --> 06:25.044
I did pay attention
in Sunday school.

06:26.637 --> 06:29.094
[ Sniffs and clears throat ]

06:36.856 --> 06:39.472
-Now, that, I like for the house...
-Mm-hm.

06:39.483 --> 06:41.565
-In the backyard.
-We'll take anything you've painted.

06:41.777 --> 06:42.983
Money's no object.

06:43.404 --> 06:45.110
WOMAN:
Really? Since when?

06:45.531 --> 06:48.113
Elise, I make six figures
drinking blood on the net.

06:48.117 --> 06:50.153
Yeah, I know you do.
I wish you didn't.

06:50.369 --> 06:52.234
-Why? It's not cheating.
-Maybe not to you, it isn't.

06:52.413 --> 06:54.324
You know what, I'm just
gonna leave you, um...

06:55.916 --> 06:57.998
[ Customer chatter ]

06:59.295 --> 07:01.160
I haven't seen this much
black nail polish

07:01.171 --> 07:02.627
since I worked the make up counter
in the '905.

07:02.798 --> 07:04.038
I know.
Can you believe this?

07:04.383 --> 07:06.715
And what is this, exactly?

07:07.219 --> 07:08.083
Happy Halloween?

07:08.470 --> 07:09.425
Huh?

07:09.597 --> 07:10.757
Speaking of...

07:11.765 --> 07:14.051
I wasn't gonna throw one
this year, but...

07:14.393 --> 07:15.849
-You're doing it for Justin?
-Yeah.

07:17.062 --> 07:17.847
Yeah.

07:18.147 --> 07:19.853
Halloween was like, uh,

07:20.107 --> 07:25.022
Christmas, and id, and a drag show
all rolled into one for him.

07:25.571 --> 07:28.313
So, it felt sort of wrong,
not celebrating it.

07:28.324 --> 07:30.110
You know...

07:31.410 --> 07:32.274
[ Sighs ]

07:32.536 --> 07:34.447
Anywho, uh...

07:34.622 --> 07:37.284
Seeing as how I forgot
my garlic and holy water,

07:37.291 --> 07:39.782
I... should make like Dracula
and fly.

07:39.793 --> 07:42.284
But I will see you at The Eh Frame
tomorrow night.

07:42.296 --> 07:44.207
-Hmm.
-Yes. Sarah?

07:44.214 --> 07:45.670
No, you know,
I just want to stay in bed

07:45.674 --> 07:46.538
and eat my weight in candy.

07:46.717 --> 07:47.832
Babe, it's your birthday.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.003
Exactly.

07:50.137 --> 07:51.126
I'm not giving up on you.

07:51.555 --> 07:53.762
You will be doing the Monster Mash
with me tomorrow night.

07:53.766 --> 07:55.597
Yeah, you know what?
Just dream big.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.765
[ Robin laughs maniacally]

07:59.021 --> 08:02.104
[ Panting ]

08:11.033 --> 08:13.319
ALAN: Looking in fine form, son.

08:13.619 --> 08:15.075
[ Exhales deeply ]

08:17.665 --> 08:19.280
Whatta ya want?

08:22.962 --> 08:24.577
Talk for a minute?

08:28.300 --> 08:29.676
I can't even imagine...

08:30.135 --> 08:32.547
how upset you still must be.

08:34.682 --> 08:36.013
About June?

08:36.934 --> 08:38.970
That was three months ago, Dad.

08:39.228 --> 08:42.186
It took me years to get over
the death of your mother, Cam.

08:44.233 --> 08:45.473
Well...

08:45.901 --> 08:48.187
Mourning won't bring June back.

08:48.779 --> 08:50.110
Didn't bring back Mom.

08:51.657 --> 08:52.612
That's true.

08:52.866 --> 08:53.992
But-II

08:56.912 --> 08:58.152
What?

09:00.666 --> 09:02.076
You and Sarah...

09:03.585 --> 09:06.452
I'm worried you might be
rushing into something...

09:08.090 --> 09:09.705
unseemly.

09:13.262 --> 09:14.627
[ Exhales deeply ]

09:25.065 --> 09:26.771
[ Drops dumbbells ]

09:33.532 --> 09:34.692
ReaHy?

09:36.452 --> 09:38.067
Tell me something, Dad.

09:38.912 --> 09:41.654
Are you this righteous when you're
down on your hands and knees

09:41.665 --> 09:43.530
being whipped and flogged
with a dog collar

09:43.542 --> 09:45.783
around that perverted little neck
of yours?

09:46.879 --> 09:48.585
Hmm?

09:53.302 --> 09:54.508
[ Groans]

09:55.387 --> 09:57.002
[ Groaning ]

10:06.690 --> 10:08.146
Hey...

10:08.358 --> 10:09.643
You know, I'm...

10:09.651 --> 10:11.391
I'm headed downtown.
I could...

10:11.695 --> 10:13.856
I could give you a ride
to the church, if you want.

10:14.782 --> 10:16.943
No, I'm fine. You go.

10:17.284 --> 10:18.399
All right.

10:19.119 --> 10:20.575
Suit yourself.

10:21.080 --> 10:21.865
[ Sighs ]

10:25.417 --> 10:26.577
[ Sighs ]

10:29.254 --> 10:30.994
[ Door opening ]

10:33.425 --> 10:34.631
[ Door closing ]

10:35.052 --> 10:37.794
[ Birds chirping ]

10:38.514 --> 10:39.674
-[ Car door closing ]
-[ Sighs ]

10:39.848 --> 10:41.554
[ Engine starting ]

11:16.802 --> 11:18.588
[ Sighs ]

11:27.187 --> 11:28.347
[ Sighs ]

11:38.657 --> 11:39.863
[ Gasps ]

11:43.162 --> 11:46.245
[ Crying ]

11:48.876 --> 11:51.618
I'm sorry, there's none
of my own work left.

11:52.171 --> 11:53.911
Let me guess,
the "vamps" got here first.

11:54.089 --> 11:54.874
[ Laughs ]

11:55.048 --> 11:56.504
Um, I do have a website,

11:56.842 --> 11:58.707
then when more become available,
you can buy them online.

12:01.972 --> 12:02.927
[ Door closing ]

12:02.931 --> 12:05.422
Could you... just excuse me
for a second?

12:08.687 --> 12:09.802
DYLAN: Hey.

12:11.190 --> 12:12.225
What are you doing here?

12:13.483 --> 12:14.768
What am I...?

12:14.776 --> 12:16.687
I've been calling for days.
You're not answering your phone.

12:16.987 --> 12:18.193
Because I don't want to
talk to you.

12:18.405 --> 12:19.941
-It's your birthday, babe.
-Yeah.

12:20.449 --> 12:23.236
Best present you can give me
is just to leave me alone.

12:24.119 --> 12:25.905
Sarah, listen.
I screwed up.

12:26.121 --> 12:27.452
I admit that.

12:27.456 --> 12:29.367
I don't even have the words
to express how sorr...

12:29.374 --> 12:30.705
[ Laughing ]
You don't have the words.

12:30.709 --> 12:31.994
Listen, babe.

12:32.461 --> 12:35.419
You wanted me...
to remove myself from the story.

12:35.422 --> 12:36.628
I did that.

12:36.632 --> 12:38.338
You wanted me
to cut ties with Lisa-Ann?

12:38.342 --> 12:39.252
I did that, too.

12:39.259 --> 12:43.423
All I am now is the editor
of a simple small town paper,

12:43.430 --> 12:44.590
and I'm fine with that.

12:53.023 --> 12:54.479
[ Phone beeping ]

13:02.241 --> 13:03.447
[ Sighs ]

13:06.662 --> 13:09.574
Sarah, you are the single
most important thing to me

13:09.998 --> 13:11.078
in the world.

13:12.042 --> 13:13.282
And you only came
to that conclusion

13:13.293 --> 13:14.669
after everything
had gone to hell?

13:14.670 --> 13:15.705
That's not true.

13:16.797 --> 13:18.503
It's too little, too late.

13:21.760 --> 13:22.840
Now, please.

13:23.178 --> 13:24.042
I'd like you to leave.

13:24.513 --> 13:25.844
Sarah.

13:38.568 --> 13:40.104
[ Customer chatter ]

13:40.112 --> 13:41.568
[ Sighs ]

13:46.785 --> 13:48.650
[ Door slams shut ]

13:55.836 --> 13:57.326
Come, Cameron.

13:57.879 --> 13:58.959
[ Sniffs ]

13:58.964 --> 14:00.829
Come and pray with me.

14:01.717 --> 14:03.548
[ Exhales deeply ]

14:04.011 --> 14:06.753
[ Softly crying ]

14:12.936 --> 14:15.678
"Have mercy upon me, O God,

14:15.856 --> 14:18.017
according
to Your loving kindness:

14:18.734 --> 14:21.316
according to the multitude
of Thy tender mercies

14:21.320 --> 14:23.311
blot out my transgressions.

14:24.698 --> 14:27.735
Wash me thoroughly
of mine iniquity,

14:27.743 --> 14:29.449
and cleanse me of my sin.

14:31.538 --> 14:33.904
For I acknowledge
my transgressions:

14:34.541 --> 14:36.873
and my sin is ever before me."

14:39.129 --> 14:40.414
[ Alan shudders ]

14:42.382 --> 14:43.542
Dad?

14:45.135 --> 14:46.124
Why are you crying?

14:46.511 --> 14:47.887
[ Sobbing ]

14:48.430 --> 14:50.216
Dad?

14:50.223 --> 14:51.474
[ Continued sobbing ]

14:52.726 --> 14:54.182
I'm sorry.

15:00.776 --> 15:02.016
[ Sighs ]

15:07.491 --> 15:09.231
You know, some parents...

15:10.035 --> 15:11.696
It takes time
to love their children.

15:13.080 --> 15:14.786
Your mother was like that.

15:16.124 --> 15:17.409
But me...

15:18.085 --> 15:19.871
The moment I saw you,

15:20.170 --> 15:22.001
my whole life finally
made sense.

15:22.005 --> 15:23.165
[ Sniffs ]

15:24.633 --> 15:26.874
Cam, was I a good father?

15:28.470 --> 15:30.586
Yeah, of course.

15:30.889 --> 15:31.924
Are you sure?

15:32.265 --> 15:33.641
'Cause I worry.

15:35.060 --> 15:37.676
I worry I didn't do everything
I needed to do for you.

15:38.814 --> 15:40.020
Dad...

15:40.399 --> 15:43.061
you're-- you're acting
really strange.

15:43.985 --> 15:45.145
[ Sobbing ]

15:46.029 --> 15:48.361
I hoped you'd forget
about that night.

15:49.491 --> 15:51.732
I thought it better just...

15:52.536 --> 15:54.276
just to move forward.

15:55.414 --> 15:58.952
[ Sighs ] But now I don 't think
that was the right thing to do.

16:00.961 --> 16:02.121
[ Sniffs ]

16:02.546 --> 16:03.661
[ Sighs ]

16:04.131 --> 16:05.871
I'm not angry at you, son.

16:06.091 --> 16:07.251
I'm not.

16:08.760 --> 16:10.261
I'm no angel.

16:10.929 --> 16:12.430
Far from it.

16:13.515 --> 16:16.097
And those people
and their sins...

16:17.686 --> 16:19.222
Who knows, a 100 years ago,

16:19.229 --> 16:21.436
maybe the state
would have put 'em to death.

16:24.151 --> 16:26.358
But you broke man's law, Cam.

16:29.990 --> 16:31.946
More importantly,
you broke God's law.

16:32.284 --> 16:33.444
Hmm.

16:34.786 --> 16:36.697
But I can help you with that.

16:37.831 --> 16:38.820
We can ask God,

16:39.124 --> 16:41.080
to forgive you, together.

16:43.003 --> 16:45.085
[ Sighs ]

16:46.756 --> 16:48.621
And what happens after that?

16:50.051 --> 16:51.177
Hmm?

16:56.057 --> 16:57.308
I'm sorry.

17:05.108 --> 17:09.647
"Lord of grace and truth,
we confess our unworthiness

17:09.863 --> 17:12.696
to stand in Your presence
as Your children.

17:14.493 --> 17:15.403
[ Sobbing ]

17:15.410 --> 17:17.025
We have sinned.

17:18.455 --> 17:22.164
Forgive... and heal us."

17:24.044 --> 17:25.534
[ Continued sobbing ]

17:27.297 --> 17:28.503
[ Choking ]
Cam!

17:29.424 --> 17:31.164
You know I'm terrible.

17:31.718 --> 17:33.549
I am not!

17:35.013 --> 17:35.763
-[ Choking ]
-Goddamnit.

17:37.349 --> 17:38.805
Goddamnit.

17:39.267 --> 17:40.052
[ Continued choking ]

17:41.144 --> 17:42.179
[ Groans]

17:50.195 --> 17:51.401
[ Gasping ]

17:58.828 --> 18:00.204
[ Exhales deeply ]

18:01.248 --> 18:02.488
Goddamnit.

18:02.916 --> 18:04.076
[ Sobbing ]

18:04.417 --> 18:06.123
Forgive me, God.

18:07.379 --> 18:09.335
[ Continued sobbing ]

18:12.384 --> 18:14.249
No one else needed to die.

18:42.539 --> 18:43.494
[ Thud at the door ]

18:43.873 --> 18:45.204
[ Bicycle bell ringing ]

18:59.431 --> 19:00.386
DYLAN: Tennyson wrote,

19:00.807 --> 19:02.763
"'Tis better to have loved
and lost

19:03.143 --> 19:05.225
than to never have loved at all. "

19:05.770 --> 19:06.555
Well, guess what?

19:06.938 --> 19:09.350
Lord Tennyson had no idea
what he was talking about.

19:10.567 --> 19:13.479
Waterbury has faced many losses
this year. But...

19:13.737 --> 19:16.945
For me, my own personal loss
has been my wife.

19:17.532 --> 19:20.945
I didn't lose her
to The Executioner, however.

19:20.952 --> 19:22.943
I lost her to myself.

19:22.954 --> 19:24.865
The greatest sin,
the cardinal sin...

19:25.040 --> 19:26.200
SHARMA: "...is pride.

19:26.207 --> 19:28.914
It's been the downfall
of many a man and woman,

19:29.294 --> 19:32.707
and now it's my own
personal undoing."

19:33.423 --> 19:34.287
Wow.

19:36.176 --> 19:36.961
[ Phone ringing ]

19:37.344 --> 19:40.177
God, if Sarah doesn't
take him back, I will.

19:41.056 --> 19:42.887
Don't you have
any actual work to do?

19:43.433 --> 19:45.173
[ Birds chirping ]

19:47.896 --> 19:49.557
You know, it was romantic,
and it was brave.

19:49.731 --> 19:51.346
I do appreciate the sentiment.

19:54.819 --> 19:56.901
thinking you'd magically
change your mind, Sarah.

19:56.905 --> 19:57.940
I wrote it
so you'd hear me out.

19:57.947 --> 19:59.812
You know, what,
yeah, and I want to believe you

19:59.824 --> 20:02.566
in the spirit
that it was written in, but...

20:02.869 --> 20:04.825
You know you lied to me.

20:05.372 --> 20:06.657
For years.

20:06.665 --> 20:07.996
[ Softly ]
Yeah.

20:09.542 --> 20:11.999
I just... I just wish
we'd never come here.

20:13.505 --> 20:16.588
You know what? I'd still be a liar,
even if we had.

20:19.928 --> 20:21.509
I'm glad--
I'm glad we came here.

20:21.513 --> 20:24.050
Because... you wanted
the truth, Sarah.

20:24.057 --> 20:25.547
And-- and you got it.

20:26.351 --> 20:27.841
Maybe more truth
than you bargained for.

20:28.228 --> 20:30.264
[ Birds squawking ]

20:31.064 --> 20:32.429
What are you talking about?

20:34.776 --> 20:36.892
This is me, Sarah.

20:37.362 --> 20:39.273
I have nothin' left to hide.

20:39.531 --> 20:41.943
For the first time
since we've met.

20:43.952 --> 20:45.533
And the irony is...

20:46.413 --> 20:47.994
we had a better shot
of making it,

20:47.997 --> 20:49.282
if we met now.

21:02.095 --> 21:04.302
[ Birds chirping ]

21:13.857 --> 21:15.518
[ Picking the lock ]

21:19.738 --> 21:20.602
[ Door unlocks ]

22:21.007 --> 22:22.793
Or we could do a piece
on what to do

22:22.801 --> 22:24.507
with all your Halloween crap
the day after.

22:24.511 --> 22:26.297
Right?
Like the Jack-o'-Iantern,

22:26.554 --> 22:28.510
all the candy you don't want
your kids to scarf down.

22:28.515 --> 22:30.676
Maybe recycling your costume
into your bedroom.

22:31.059 --> 22:32.014
Sound fun?

22:32.310 --> 22:33.766
-Whoa! Whoa!
-CAM: Get down on the ground!

22:33.770 --> 22:35.135
-OFFICER: Nobody move!
-Get down on the ground!

22:35.313 --> 22:36.223
Cam, what's...?
What...?

22:36.231 --> 22:37.846
Dylan Bennett,
you are under arrest for murder.

22:37.857 --> 22:38.972
What are you talking about?
There's a mistake.

22:39.150 --> 22:40.230
This is a mistake!

22:40.235 --> 22:41.020
[ Groans]

22:41.236 --> 22:42.976
Verna McBride, Justin Faysal...

22:42.987 --> 22:44.488
-CAM: Brenda Merritt...
-You're making a mistake.

22:44.489 --> 22:45.899
CAM: Trent McBride.

22:46.574 --> 22:49.111
June Henry...
You sick son of a bitch!

22:50.078 --> 22:53.366
Alison Sutherland, Iain Vaughn,
and Tom Winston.

22:53.373 --> 22:55.159
C-- Call Sarah.

22:55.166 --> 22:56.667
Tell her to meet me
at the station.

23:00.171 --> 23:01.877
-Thanks.
-No problem.

23:02.465 --> 23:03.500
Hey, Sarah.

23:06.845 --> 23:08.005
[ Sighs ]

23:09.889 --> 23:11.425
I don't understand.

23:14.143 --> 23:17.010
Just take it easy. Okay?

23:17.021 --> 23:18.602
Breathe.

23:19.524 --> 23:21.060
SHARMA: Chief?

23:21.067 --> 23:22.056
We're done here.

23:22.235 --> 23:23.475
Want me to take Sarah
to the hotel?

23:23.486 --> 23:24.441
We have to impound their car.

23:25.697 --> 23:26.686
Uh...

23:27.448 --> 23:28.904
No. Thanks, I got it.

23:29.492 --> 23:31.778
Just, uh... We're good.

23:31.995 --> 23:32.859
Thanks, Sharma.

23:35.206 --> 23:36.616
You're gonna be okay.

23:38.918 --> 23:40.374
It's like he wanted me
to find them.

23:41.963 --> 23:43.544
To punish me.

23:46.092 --> 23:48.128
Or maybe he wanted
to be caught.

23:48.970 --> 23:50.176
I don't understand.

23:50.513 --> 23:51.502
Sarah...

23:52.724 --> 23:56.558
There's no telling what goes on
in the mind of a... a criminal.

23:59.397 --> 24:01.433
[ Crying ]
I just want to close my eyes

24:02.567 --> 24:04.478
and never open them.

24:05.445 --> 24:06.275
You go ahead.

24:06.779 --> 24:07.985
I'm here.

24:08.656 --> 24:10.863
I'm here,
and I'm not going anywhere.

24:11.868 --> 24:13.984
[ Sobbing ]

24:18.958 --> 24:20.869
We married the wrong people.

24:24.005 --> 24:25.245
I should have waited for you.

24:27.008 --> 24:28.373
And now...

24:29.052 --> 24:30.713
I can never tell if...

24:31.262 --> 24:33.048
you felt the way I did.

24:33.932 --> 24:35.263
[ Sighs ]

24:35.808 --> 24:37.844
-I should have been more brave.
-No.

24:40.063 --> 24:42.054
You are brave, Cam.
You're the...

24:43.608 --> 24:45.439
You're the bravest man I know.

24:47.654 --> 24:51.272
[ Birds chirping ]

24:58.623 --> 24:59.988
Sarah, maybe--
maybe we should...

24:59.999 --> 25:00.784
No.

25:34.742 --> 25:36.528
[ Moaning ]

26:02.979 --> 26:06.016
[ Panting ]

26:15.199 --> 26:16.905
CAM: I was thinkin'...

26:17.452 --> 26:19.363
I'll go spend a few hours
with Dylan.

26:20.038 --> 26:22.450
See what-- see what
I can find out.

26:23.166 --> 26:25.327
And I thought,
maybe afterwards...

26:25.543 --> 26:27.534
we come back here,
order some food?

26:28.463 --> 26:30.579
I actually just need to be alone.

26:33.384 --> 26:34.669
Huh?

26:35.470 --> 26:36.710
Well...

26:37.221 --> 26:38.677
It's been a long day.

26:40.850 --> 26:43.432
Why don't you call me
if you change your mind, okay?

26:52.570 --> 26:54.071
[ Birds chirping ]

26:54.947 --> 26:56.938
[ Door opening ]

26:57.492 --> 26:58.948
[ Door closing ]

27:00.453 --> 27:02.193
[ Kids yelling ]

27:02.872 --> 27:04.954
[ Dog barking ]

27:11.089 --> 27:12.249
Now...

27:12.715 --> 27:14.797
Why don't you tell me
why we found a box

27:14.801 --> 27:16.712
full of evidence
in your house?

27:17.053 --> 27:18.463
What the hell
are you talking about?

27:23.893 --> 27:26.134
Do you deny
that this is your box?

27:26.479 --> 27:27.264
Hmm?

27:27.730 --> 27:28.719
Or is it Sarah's?

27:29.148 --> 27:29.978
Okay.

27:30.191 --> 27:31.146
I need to talk to my lawyer.

27:31.609 --> 27:33.474
No, you need to tell me
why you kept a box

27:33.486 --> 27:35.602
full of goddamn souvenirs
from the murder scenes.

27:39.408 --> 27:41.694
Brenda Merritt's fingernails.

27:42.120 --> 27:44.827
Tell me, Dylan, did you--
you pull those out with pliers?

27:45.123 --> 27:46.454
No! Cam, listen to me.

27:46.624 --> 27:48.034
I didn't do anything
to anybody, Cam.

27:48.042 --> 27:48.952
You have the wrong guy.

27:49.210 --> 27:50.495
What about my wife's hair, huh?

27:50.670 --> 27:52.456
Okay, I need to see my lawyer.

27:53.131 --> 27:54.246
Now!

27:57.426 --> 27:58.711
Yeah...

27:59.262 --> 28:00.672
Maybe I'll do that...

28:05.101 --> 28:06.386
tomorrow.

28:07.353 --> 28:08.308
You better get used to that chair

28:08.312 --> 28:09.427
because you're gonna
be there all night.

28:09.438 --> 28:11.053
Cam, listen to me.

28:11.065 --> 28:11.850
Cam!

28:12.108 --> 28:13.769
PIea-- Hear me out!

29:18.466 --> 29:19.922
[ Clicked on tablet ]

29:44.367 --> 29:45.948
[ Trick or treater chatter ]

30:00.633 --> 30:01.873
Yeah.

30:02.176 --> 30:03.131
Cam.

30:03.552 --> 30:05.463
-He framed me?
-He's trying to.

30:05.680 --> 30:06.544
We've got hard evidence.

30:06.806 --> 30:08.421
No.
Sarah, we have a painting.

30:08.432 --> 30:09.342
We have a theory.

30:09.767 --> 30:12.008
-We don't have near enough proof.
-Well, then, I'll find the proof.

30:12.228 --> 30:13.559
No, Sarah.

30:13.938 --> 30:14.848
Find a lawyer.

30:15.064 --> 30:17.350
They'll find someone
who outranks Cam,

30:17.358 --> 30:18.393
and we'll handle it that way.

30:18.401 --> 30:19.390
By the time that happens,

30:19.402 --> 30:21.233
you'll be found hanging
in your cell.

30:21.237 --> 30:22.443
Hey, listen,
I will find you a lawyer.

30:22.697 --> 30:25.029
-No! Sarah, please.
-I'm not waiting, anymore.

30:25.241 --> 30:26.902
Babe, do not go...
Don't leave, Sarah!

30:26.909 --> 30:28.069
It's not safe!

30:28.327 --> 30:30.488
GIRL: Trick or treat!

30:31.580 --> 30:34.117
[ Trick or treater chatter ]

30:34.750 --> 30:37.082
-MAN: This is it, all right?
-CHILD: Okay.

30:37.962 --> 30:39.293
GIRL: Trick or treat!

32:52.513 --> 32:53.719
[ Sloshing noise ]

33:49.403 --> 33:51.769
91 1 OPERA TOR:
911. What is your emergency?

33:54.200 --> 33:54.985
Hello?

33:55.326 --> 33:56.486
Are you there?

33:58.621 --> 33:59.827
Hello?

34:00.664 --> 34:01.995
[ Hangs up phone ]

34:22.394 --> 34:24.350
[ Music playing ]

34:52.675 --> 34:53.710
Merlin! Merlin! Cut!

34:53.884 --> 34:54.794
[ Music ends ]

34:54.802 --> 34:56.258
[ Clears throat ]
Uh, sorry, everyone.

34:56.595 --> 34:59.211
Uh, I didn't mean to stop
the dancing. Just one second.

34:59.223 --> 35:00.759
I just wanted to thank you all...

35:01.225 --> 35:02.465
so, so much for coming.

35:02.476 --> 35:03.682
-I really appreciate it.
-MAN: Whoo!

35:03.686 --> 35:04.471
-WOMAN: Yeah!
-Um...

35:04.728 --> 35:06.309
You probably didn't know this...

35:06.313 --> 35:08.053
I didn't, but...

35:08.274 --> 35:11.482
Halloween, actually started
as a celebration of life.

35:12.069 --> 35:12.819
We would, um,

35:13.320 --> 35:16.312
wear costumes...
to scare off death.

35:17.199 --> 35:17.949
Well, some of us do.

35:18.117 --> 35:20.950
Some of us actually dress up
like hot firemen and sexy nurses,

35:20.953 --> 35:22.193
so we can get laid tonight.

35:22.538 --> 35:23.948
Right? I see you.

35:24.123 --> 35:25.363
I see you over there.

35:25.541 --> 35:26.621
Um...

35:27.376 --> 35:28.707
[ Clears throat ]

35:29.128 --> 35:30.618
I, uh...

35:33.299 --> 35:35.631
I lost the love of my life
this year.

35:37.845 --> 35:39.130
And I've...

35:39.805 --> 35:42.171
I've felt very powerless,
ever since.

35:43.601 --> 35:44.761
[ Sniffs ]

35:45.019 --> 35:46.475
But tonight...
[ Laughs ]

35:46.687 --> 35:47.893
Tonight I am giving...

35:48.355 --> 35:50.971
a great big middle finger
to death because...

35:51.525 --> 35:52.435
[ Sighs ]

35:52.443 --> 35:54.058
Because I'm still here.

35:54.737 --> 35:55.943
-MAN: That's right.
-MAN 2: You bet.

35:56.363 --> 35:58.103
ROBIN: We are still here.

35:59.450 --> 36:00.235
[ Sighs ]

36:01.619 --> 36:03.155
50, Justin...

36:04.747 --> 36:06.954
Wherever you are,
I really hope...

36:07.291 --> 36:10.124
that you can see us celebrating
your favorite holiday.

36:12.212 --> 36:13.713
As we raise our glass to you...

36:14.173 --> 36:15.162
ALL: Justin.

36:15.883 --> 36:17.589
Happy Halloween!

36:18.010 --> 36:19.341
[ Hoots and hollering ]

36:19.511 --> 36:20.887
Let's party!

36:21.263 --> 36:22.013
Merlin!

36:22.181 --> 36:23.466
[ Music starts again ]

36:26.352 --> 36:27.592
-SARAH: Robin?
-Honey, honey, honey.

36:27.603 --> 36:28.638
ROBIN: I've got some very
disturbing news.

36:28.646 --> 36:29.681
Listen, is Cam here?

36:29.688 --> 36:31.144
I".yeah.

36:34.026 --> 36:35.232
Would you look at that?

36:35.819 --> 36:37.901
Listen, I don't believe you.
Dylan can't be The Execu...

36:37.905 --> 36:38.985
Yeah, he's not, okay?

36:38.989 --> 36:39.944
But even if he is,

36:39.948 --> 36:41.529
I want you to know
I'm here for you, okay?

36:41.533 --> 36:42.818
-You're a victim, too.
-Okay.

36:42.826 --> 36:43.611
Yeah, thanks.

36:43.911 --> 36:46.823
[ Music continues playing ]

36:51.460 --> 36:52.245
Hey!

36:52.670 --> 36:53.580
What are you doing here?

36:53.587 --> 36:54.793
I thought you were gonna
lay low tonight?

36:55.005 --> 36:57.291
Well, I thought you'd be
at the police station.

36:58.175 --> 37:00.712
I decided to let Dylan
stew for a bit.

37:01.303 --> 37:04.136
He's—- he's lying
through his teeth.

37:04.348 --> 37:06.009
Denied everything.

37:06.975 --> 37:08.556
But I'm gonna break him.

37:11.188 --> 37:12.849
Do you wanna go outside?

37:16.568 --> 37:17.648
The party's in here.

37:18.612 --> 37:19.897
Exactly.

37:22.866 --> 37:24.072
Is everything okay, Sarah?

37:24.827 --> 37:26.237
Never better.

37:27.079 --> 37:28.319
Come on.

37:37.840 --> 37:39.501
Wait.
Where are you taking me?

37:39.800 --> 37:41.336
What's with all the questions,
huh?

37:42.094 --> 37:43.834
Aren't you supposed to be
interrogating, Dylan?

37:53.272 --> 37:54.978
No, no, wait.

37:56.525 --> 37:58.436
Are you sure, you're okay
with this, Sarah?

37:59.611 --> 38:01.693
You mean, go back inside?

38:02.281 --> 38:03.066
No.

38:03.407 --> 38:04.817
Then, shut up.

38:18.547 --> 38:20.128
-[ Stabbing sound ]
-[ Groaning ]

38:20.966 --> 38:22.046
[ Panting ]

38:32.144 --> 38:33.634
What did you do to me?

38:35.522 --> 38:36.682
What did I do to you?

38:38.442 --> 38:39.807
What did I do to you?!

38:41.278 --> 38:42.233
What the hell's going on?

38:42.404 --> 38:43.519
Robin? No, no, Robin.

38:44.364 --> 38:45.615
-[ Stabbing sound ]
-[ Groaning ]

38:45.616 --> 38:46.401
Robin!

38:48.202 --> 38:49.032
[ Groaning ]

38:49.203 --> 38:50.033
[ Screaming ]
No!

38:51.371 --> 38:53.498
Hey, what's going on
down there?

38:59.004 --> 39:00.995
-Someone call 911.
-What the hell?

39:02.382 --> 39:03.417
Sharma!

39:03.425 --> 39:05.040
Let me out of here!

39:05.928 --> 39:07.088
[ Sighs ]

39:08.096 --> 39:09.677
[ Continues to sigh ]
[ Door opening ]

39:12.059 --> 39:13.595
Your wife called.

39:14.812 --> 39:15.722
Pardon the outfit.

39:16.021 --> 39:17.261
I assure you,
I am a lawyer.

39:17.648 --> 39:18.808
Can you tell him
to let me out of here?

39:19.149 --> 39:21.310
I'm sorry, I can't do anything
until I can reach Chief Henry.

39:21.485 --> 39:23.146
I have brought with me
a writ of habeas corpus.

39:23.320 --> 39:24.526
Do you have any idea
what that means?

39:26.073 --> 39:26.903
No.

39:27.574 --> 39:28.529
It means...

39:29.076 --> 39:31.192
either you charge my client
with an actual crime

39:31.203 --> 39:32.283
or you release him.

39:32.579 --> 39:33.659
You can't just keep him here.

39:34.873 --> 39:37.205
I don't-- I don't have the authority
to do anything.

39:37.209 --> 39:38.164
Fine.

39:38.168 --> 39:39.123
I'll make a decision for you.

39:39.127 --> 39:40.503
Mr. Bennett.

39:41.129 --> 39:41.914
SHARMA: Wha...?

39:42.130 --> 39:43.666
-Thank you.
-Wait, um...

39:43.674 --> 39:44.629
Good evening.

39:46.051 --> 39:47.507
Shit.

39:56.812 --> 39:58.143
Help!

40:02.401 --> 40:03.140
[ Groaning ]

40:07.406 --> 40:09.192
[ Crying ]

40:21.253 --> 40:22.493
[ Drops keys ]

40:24.798 --> 40:26.208
911 OPERATOR:
911. What's your emergency?

40:26.508 --> 40:27.258
SARAH: Please,
you've got to help me.

40:27.426 --> 40:28.757
The Executioner, he's here.

40:28.760 --> 40:29.715
91 1 OPERA TOR:
I 'm sorry?

40:29.720 --> 40:31.631
-Help!
-911 OPERATOR: Are you there?

40:31.638 --> 40:33.048
This is Sarah Bennett!
He's outside!

40:33.265 --> 40:34.380
He's trying to kill me!

40:34.766 --> 40:36.176
911 OPERATOR:
Are you in danger?

40:37.144 --> 40:37.929
Ma 'a
m?

40:42.107 --> 40:43.267
SARAH: No!

40:48.488 --> 40:50.274
[ Screaming ]

40:54.453 --> 40:55.568
Open the door, Sarah.

40:59.833 --> 41:01.573
[ Screaming ]
Open the goddamn door!

41:01.877 --> 41:03.663
[ Screaming ]
Get out!

41:10.636 --> 41:12.172
-[ Thud at door ]
-[ Screams ]

41:19.186 --> 41:19.971
[ Grunting ]

41:20.354 --> 41:21.469
[ Knife hits the ground ]

41:22.940 --> 41:23.725
DYLAN: Sarah!

41:25.609 --> 41:27.270
Go! Get help now!

41:27.945 --> 41:28.855
No!

41:28.862 --> 41:30.773
SARAH: No! Don't! Don't!

41:31.448 --> 41:32.198
[ Grunting ]

41:32.366 --> 41:34.072
No! Don't!

41:34.242 --> 41:35.231
[ Continued grunting ]

41:39.081 --> 41:39.866
No!

41:43.043 --> 41:43.907
[ Gasping ]

41:44.795 --> 41:45.580
[ Screams ]

41:47.839 --> 41:49.795
[ Continued screaming ]

41:53.011 --> 41:55.593
[ Sobbing ]

41:57.516 --> 41:59.757
-[ Sarah groaning]
-This isn't what I wanted.

42:00.060 --> 42:01.925
This is the exact opposite
of what I wanted!

42:02.688 --> 42:04.303
[ Whimpering ]

42:06.483 --> 42:08.144
I-- I ruined this!

42:08.568 --> 42:09.432
[ Sobbing ]

42:09.611 --> 42:11.067
I ruin everything!

42:12.239 --> 42:14.696
[Cam yelling]
I ruin everything!

42:18.328 --> 42:20.034
[ Gasping ]

42:26.962 --> 42:29.248
I'm gonna rest here, okay?

42:32.718 --> 42:33.503
[ Sighs ]

42:39.516 --> 42:40.266
Hey.

42:41.435 --> 42:42.220
Sarah.

42:42.602 --> 42:45.389
Did I tell you about the first time
I saw you, Sarah?

42:47.024 --> 42:47.809
[ Sighs ]

42:48.734 --> 42:50.349
Camp Motega.

42:55.282 --> 42:57.398
And you were sitting by the lake,

42:57.617 --> 42:59.824
running your fingers
through the water.

43:01.747 --> 43:02.532
[ Sighs ]

43:02.789 --> 43:03.778
In the air...

43:05.250 --> 43:07.115
I don't know,
I guess it was...

43:07.753 --> 43:10.335
I guess it was dandelion seeds
or something, but...

43:11.798 --> 43:13.208
Ah, just these...

43:14.009 --> 43:15.715
white flecks...

43:16.219 --> 43:17.334
flowing...

43:18.430 --> 43:20.386
glowing in the sun.

43:21.600 --> 43:22.806
[ Groaning ]

43:24.394 --> 43:26.726
[ Gasping ]

43:28.815 --> 43:29.804
You don't think...

43:32.736 --> 43:35.022
I just...

43:35.030 --> 43:36.110
[ Groaning ]

43:36.114 --> 43:37.900
You know, I stopped.

43:39.367 --> 43:41.358
And I watched you.

43:43.121 --> 43:45.658
You were just so perfect.

43:47.459 --> 43:48.995
P...?

43:49.002 --> 43:50.583
Perfect?

43:51.713 --> 43:52.919
-CAM: Yeah.
-No.

43:53.715 --> 43:56.923
You're just so... pure.

43:57.094 --> 43:58.209
[ Sarah whimpering ]

43:58.386 --> 44:00.923
And... innocent, you know?

44:01.973 --> 44:03.224
Perfect.

44:03.683 --> 44:04.889
[ Groaning ]

44:06.770 --> 44:07.976
Hmm.

44:10.732 --> 44:12.017
Well...

44:12.025 --> 44:13.765
[ Continued whimpering ]

44:17.280 --> 44:18.486
[ Sighs ]

44:23.787 --> 44:25.823
[ Groaning ]

44:33.839 --> 44:35.045
I'm sorry.

44:36.883 --> 44:37.713
[ Screaming ]

44:38.009 --> 44:39.465
-[ Metal clank]
-[ Groan ]

44:41.847 --> 44:43.462
[ Sobbing ]

45:05.829 --> 45:06.614
Sarah!

45:07.664 --> 45:09.700
[Cam groaning]

45:18.884 --> 45:20.090
[ Continued groaning ]

45:20.719 --> 45:22.380
CAM: What did you do?

45:23.305 --> 45:25.011
[ Whimpering ]

45:26.308 --> 45:27.468
[ Gasps ]

45:35.859 --> 45:36.939
DYLAN: Sarah, don't!

45:37.319 --> 45:39.651
Don't, Sarah! Don't!
Don't do it.

45:40.071 --> 45:41.777
Wh--? Why?

45:42.032 --> 45:43.488
[ Sobbing ]
Oh, why?

45:43.491 --> 45:44.697
Don't.

45:45.410 --> 45:47.116
-Because you're not a murderer.
-SARAH: No, please.

45:47.120 --> 45:48.030
No!

45:50.957 --> 45:52.458
Please, Dylan.

45:52.751 --> 45:54.662
Please, I need you to help me.

45:55.045 --> 45:57.878
-No.
-Please... help.

45:57.881 --> 45:59.587
Please, Dylan!

46:00.091 --> 46:01.706
I need you, please.

46:02.761 --> 46:04.046
[ Sobbing ]

46:05.055 --> 46:07.296
[ Whimpering ]
SARAH: Just... please!

46:09.100 --> 46:09.930
No!

46:10.101 --> 46:11.011
-[ Grunting ]
-SARAH: No!

46:11.186 --> 46:12.767
No! No!

46:12.938 --> 46:13.768
No!

46:16.650 --> 46:17.685
[ Gasping ]

46:18.485 --> 46:20.271
I don't remember meeting you,
Cam.

46:21.613 --> 46:22.602
That's not true.

46:23.156 --> 46:24.066
I remember camp.

46:24.074 --> 46:25.939
I remember
becoming friends, but...

46:26.201 --> 46:28.943
I don't remember
the first time I saw you!

46:29.496 --> 46:31.077
It was that day by the lake.

46:31.289 --> 46:33.780
See, that's just...
It was just a Saturday.

46:34.501 --> 46:36.662
I wasn't... I wasn't innocent.

46:36.670 --> 46:37.659
I wasn't pure.

46:37.671 --> 46:39.127
I was 15!

46:41.216 --> 46:42.877
I didn't know who I was.

46:43.426 --> 46:45.291
But I do now.

46:47.264 --> 46:48.470
[ Sarah crying ]
[Cam groaning]

46:52.936 --> 46:53.846
God!

46:53.853 --> 46:55.434
I'll tell you
what I'll never forget.

46:56.564 --> 46:59.306
I'll never forget
seeing my grandmother...

47:00.110 --> 47:02.021
drifting in the lake.

47:02.696 --> 47:04.607
The life draining out of her.

47:05.031 --> 47:06.020
[Cam groaning]

47:07.450 --> 47:10.112
[Cam whimpering ]

47:14.457 --> 47:16.197
-[ Grunting ]
-[ Continued groaning ]

47:16.584 --> 47:18.040
[ Continued whimpering ]
Ow!

47:19.838 --> 47:22.671
I'll never forget Justin's
last breath.

47:23.842 --> 47:27.084
Cam, June worshipped
the ground you walked on.

47:27.679 --> 47:28.794
[Cam groaning]

47:29.139 --> 47:31.004
How she trusted you...

47:33.059 --> 47:34.310
[ Gasping ]

47:35.562 --> 47:37.348
[ Police sirens approaching ]

47:38.148 --> 47:39.763
-[ Yelling ]
-[ Groaning ]

47:40.066 --> 47:41.977
[ Gasping ]

47:43.028 --> 47:44.438
SARAH: The desecration
of Verna McBride.

47:44.988 --> 47:46.603
What you did to Robin.

47:48.241 --> 47:50.653
Your father, Cam!

47:51.745 --> 47:53.701
Your father!

47:54.080 --> 47:54.910
[Cam groaning]

47:55.498 --> 47:57.750
[ Police sirens growing louder ]

47:58.335 --> 48:01.042
[ Knocks at the door ]
OFFICER: Police! Open up!

48:07.135 --> 48:08.966
-[ Knocks at the door ]
-CAM: No...

48:19.522 --> 48:21.023
Never forget.

48:21.191 --> 48:21.976
[ Groaning ]

48:29.491 --> 48:30.276
[ Drops knife ]

48:37.082 --> 48:38.913
[ Crickets chirping ]

48:45.090 --> 48:47.502
You'd never guess,
just lookin' at it.

48:48.093 --> 48:50.459
But you can feel it, right?
There's...

48:50.678 --> 48:52.054
just something wrong.

48:52.389 --> 48:53.219
[ Sighs ]

48:54.015 --> 48:56.256
Three-story executive
with bad juju.

48:57.143 --> 48:59.134
ROBIN: How 'bout we leave
that part out of the listing?

49:00.730 --> 49:02.721
You know, if it's too difficult
showing it...

49:03.191 --> 49:04.271
I gave you my word.

49:06.569 --> 49:07.399
How are you feeling?

49:08.321 --> 49:09.231
Uh...

49:09.239 --> 49:12.197
I look like Frankenstein
with my shirt off, but...

49:12.742 --> 49:13.982
I'll live.

49:14.953 --> 49:17.069
Okay, no, you can't look at me
like that.

49:17.247 --> 49:19.112
You're gonna make me cry,
and I hate crying.

49:22.335 --> 49:23.666
-You're welcome.
-I'm very sorry.

49:23.920 --> 49:25.956
Now, you stay out of trouble,
okay?

49:26.214 --> 49:28.170
Don't move
into any cursed homes.

49:28.174 --> 49:30.460
And don't... befriend anyone
with the last name

49:30.468 --> 49:32.004
"Henry," "Dahmer," or "Bundy."

49:32.554 --> 49:33.714
Deal.

49:35.265 --> 49:36.380
I'm gonna miss you, Robin.

49:37.058 --> 49:38.138
You're not.

49:38.393 --> 49:39.508
I'm gonna be crashing
on your couch

49:39.519 --> 49:40.508
every other weekend.

49:40.687 --> 49:42.018
[ Laughs ]
Right.

49:42.021 --> 49:43.431
-[ Dylan laughs]
-You take care of her!

49:43.857 --> 49:45.313
Don't worry about that.

49:45.525 --> 49:47.231
Just worry
about selling this house.

49:47.569 --> 49:48.775
[ Softly ]
All right.

50:01.040 --> 50:02.996
[ Car engine starting ]

50:19.309 --> 50:20.845
We're gonna be okay, right?

50:22.437 --> 50:23.597
Better than okay.

50:26.274 --> 50:29.016
Now find me some music,
something suitable for...

50:29.652 --> 50:31.813
Driving off into the sunset?

50:32.113 --> 50:33.273
I'll see what I can do.

50:33.990 --> 50:36.231
RADIO PREACHER: There is nothing
that keeps wicked men,

50:36.242 --> 50:38.494
at any one moment,
out of hell!

50:38.703 --> 50:41.035
-RADIO PREACHER: But the mere...
-We need a new car.

50:41.206 --> 50:43.071
-Preferably with Bluetooth.
-Yeah.

50:43.082 --> 50:44.697
You know what?
New country it is.

50:44.876 --> 50:45.706
[ Music plays ]

50:46.211 --> 50:47.872
Under his roof

50:48.421 --> 50:52.255
Mama '5 tears like rain

50:53.593 --> 50:54.878
Nowhere to run

50:55.053 --> 50:58.136
From demons like his

50:58.556 --> 51:00.171
Too young I learned

51:00.391 --> 51:03.303
Home ain't where the heart is

51:03.895 --> 51:07.137
When home
is where the hurt is

51:07.607 --> 51:08.847
The house has five bedrooms.

51:09.108 --> 51:11.099
Which, I know, sounds large
for a family of three,

51:11.110 --> 51:14.398
but think about it, you could both
have your own offices.

51:14.405 --> 51:15.611
There's bedrooms for guests.

51:15.615 --> 51:16.570
Plus, if you wanted to,

51:16.574 --> 51:18.280
you could open up
your own 3&3.

51:18.284 --> 51:20.070
-People do it all the time.
-[ Cat meowing ]

51:21.287 --> 51:23.027
-ROBIN: After you.
-[ Cat meowing ]

51:23.039 --> 51:24.495
ROBIN: The wood throughout
is original,

51:24.499 --> 51:26.535
as is all the stained glass.

51:26.709 --> 51:27.915
[ Door closing ]

51:28.628 --> 51:29.868
[ Cat continues meowing ]

51:31.506 --> 51:32.871
[ Birds chirping ]

51:35.218 --> 51:37.254
Here, kitty, kitty.

51:43.101 --> 51:45.592
-You're such a pretty cat.
-[ Cat meows ]

51:45.853 --> 51:47.104
Mmm.

51:47.313 --> 51:48.393
-[ Cat growls ]
-[ Snap ]

51:48.606 --> 51:50.267
[ Breathes deeply ]

51:52.318 --> 51:55.936
You've got all new appliances,
granite countertop, backsplash.

51:55.947 --> 51:59.235
I love, love, love this little
breakfast nook over here.

52:02.203 --> 52:03.943
What do you say, Scotia?

52:04.163 --> 52:05.198
You like this house?

52:06.165 --> 52:09.123
Yes, this house feels perfect.

52:10.920 --> 52:12.911
Nowhere to run

52:13.089 --> 52:15.956
From demons like his

52:16.134 --> 52:17.840
Too young I learned

52:18.177 --> 52:21.305
Home ain't where the heart is

52:21.556 --> 52:24.889
When home
is where the hurt is

52:25.768 --> 52:29.727
That house
is where the hurt is
